reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars High quality USB C cable
reviews.reviewText: I hadn't seen coiled USB C cables before so I decided to give these a try. They are of high quality especially the connectors at each end. The included clips to hold the cables together is a nice touch. Unstretched length is about 1 foot. I only see 2 flaws. First, the connectors hold themselves pretty well when plugged into ports but the useable length is not 3 feet but more like just under 2.5 feet. The coils are made pretty tight so that you can't get to 3 feet before the cable pulls out of a port. Second, if you stretch the cable in a direction perpendicular to the direction that it goes into a port (see photos), there is quite a bit of tension on the connection. I'm afraid that this might damage the port (or connector) over time. Otherwise the cables do the jobs they were designed to do.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is NOT USB-C. It does not fit my Iphone 12 pro max. It fits the Nintendo switch if that tells anyone anything about what the charger actually is. Such a BUMMER. I hate when things aren't accurate on here especially with what the item actually is.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Power Delivery Questionable
reviews.reviewText: So first, I did receive two USB-C to USB-C cables which were about a foot in length but stretchable for a considerable 3-4ft in lengthThese were perfect for my minivan where the driver and passenger often vie for cable ports and space.It did deliver power from car to both devices (a S23 & a Pixel), but... I did not see either device "fast charging". A fast charger can bring me from 0 to 100% in an hour+ but this cable was detected to charge from 0 to 100 in 5 hours +Super fast charging occurs at 45w, and this was supposed to transfer 60w. I'll test further but I just wanted to put that out there.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for putting in your car
reviews.reviewText: I like that this cable is coiled up so it takes less space in my car's center console. It is well made, and transfers power well. It's a good cord, and great price for the 2 pack. My only issue is that it's so tightly wound, it really only extends about 2 feet, not the advertised 3 feet.
